      "text": [
        ": سَأَلْتُ أَبَا جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنِ اَلتَّقْصِيرِ فَقَالَ «بَرِيدٌ ذَاهِبٌ وَ بَرِيدٌ جَائِي وَ كَانَ رَسُولُ اَللَّهِ صَلَّى اَللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ وَ آلِهِ إِذَا أَتَى ذُبَاباً قَصَّرَ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1303 - Jamil ibn Darraj reported from Zurarah ibn A'yan, who said:\nI asked Abu Ja'far (as) about the ruling for shortening the prayer.\nImam (as) said: \"A barid going and a barid returning. The Messenger of Allah (sw) would shorten his prayers when he reached Dhu'bāb.\""
        ]
      }
